    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In the brave new world of automated highways (news article, July 23), the computers used to program the special cars seem to be just as foolhardy as many drivers. The photo accompanying your article shows two cars zooming along, with the second car dangerously tailgating the first.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In the brave new world of automated highways (news article, July 23), the computers used to program the special cars seem to be just as foolhardy as many drivers. The photo accompanying your article shows two cars zooming along, with the second car dangerously tailgating the first.</p>
        <p>In spite of the assurances by Jim Rillings of the National Automated Highway System Consortium that once the computer takes over, ''you can just sit back and let your mind wander,'' I suspect that a computerized car traveling at high speed just a car length behind me would concentrate my thoughts most wonderfully.</p>
        <p>MICHAEL MAXTONE-GRAHAM  New York, July 23, 1997</p>
      </block>
